 delink from and oppose epistemologies of coloniality. After things fall apart, Hanchey posits, the creation of decolonial futures depends on the labor required to imagine impossible futures into being.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aDecolonizationzTanzania. 0aEthnologyxFieldworkxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aNon-governmental organizationsxHistoryzTanzania. 0aNon-governmental organizationszTanzaniaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Africa / East.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478024569?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478024569423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478024569/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles